# Sidebar Menu UI Implementation Standards

## Context

- When implementing nested sidebar menu components
- When visual hierarchy and precise styling are required
- When tree-like connector lines are needed for sub-items

## Critical Rules

- Menu Item Base Structure:
  - Height: 36px
  - Icon size: 20px
  - Padding-left: level > 0 ? 24px : 20px
  - Hover effect must not overlap connector lines

- Tree Line Specifications:
  - Main vertical line: 1px width, rgba(145, 158, 171, 0.16)
  - Position: left: 10px
  - Z-index: below menu items
  - No double lines allowed

- Horizontal Branches:
  - Width: 8px
  - Thickness: 1px
  - Color: rgba(145, 158, 171, 0.16)
  - Must align perfectly with parent item

- Visual Hierarchy:
  - Parent items: bold text
  - Child items: regular text
  - Consistent spacing between menu levels
  - Clear visual distinction between active and inactive states

## Examples

<example>
{
  const MenuItem = styled('div')`
    height: 36px;
    padding-left: ${props => props.level > 0 ? '24px' : '20px'};
    
    .icon {
      width: 20px;
      height: 20px;
    }
    
    &::before {
      content: '';
      width: 1px;
      height: 100%;
      left: 10px;
      background: rgba(145, 158, 171, 0.16);
      position: absolute;
    }
  `;
}
</example>

